description: This table represents details of Family Health Plus insurance program. Family Health Plus is a public health insurance program for adults between the ages of 19 and 64 who do not have health insurance - either on their own or through their employers - but have incomes too high to qualify for Medicaid.  The Family Health Plus Premium Assistance Program is available to help eligible lower-income employees and their families participate in their employer’s health insurance plan.
